.IX Title "CLUSTERPARTITION.CONF 1"
.TH CLUSTERPARTITION.CONF 1 "2008-02-05" "perl v5.8.8" "Kadeploy commands"
.SH "NAME"
clusterpartition.conf \- Nodes partition file.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This  file  describe the nodes partition schema. Actually you can partition only one drive. The syntax is simple, they are only three \*(L"class\*(R" of line.
.SH "LINE TYPES"
.IX Header "LINE TYPES"
The 3 different types of lines possible in this configuration file.
.IP "\fBhda size=80000\fR" 4
.IX Item "hda size=80000"
The primary master harddrive named \*(L"hda\*(R" of the specified \*(L"size\*(R" (in Mo).
.IP "\fBpart=1 size=4000 fdisktype=83 label=empty type=primary\fR" 4
.IX Item "part=1 size=4000 fdisktype=83 label=empty type=primary"
A first primary partition of 4000 Mo and fdisktype.
.IP "\fBpart=5 size=1000 fdisktype=82 label=empty type=logical\fR" 4
.IX Item "part=5 size=1000 fdisktype=82 label=empty type=logical"
A logical partition included in the extended partition...
.PP
\&\fB\s-1WARNING\s0\fR: they are a maximum of 4 primary and 0 extended or 3 primary and 1 extended.
.SH "EXAMPLE"
.IX Header "EXAMPLE"
.Vb 3
\& hda size=8000
\& part=1 size=4000  fdisktype=83 label=empty type=primary
\& part=2 size=4000  label=empty type=extended
.Ve
.PP
.Vb 2
\& part=5 size=1000   fdisktype=82 label=empty type=logical
\& part=6 size=1000   fdisktype=82 label=empty type=logical
.Ve
.PP
In this schema, you have \s-1TWO\s0 primary partitions on a 8GB \s-1IDE\s0 harddrive and Three usable partitions. The two main are 4GB, and the Three real are 4GB, 1GB and 1GB. The extended partition contain logicals partition.
